Forwarded from: ⚔️BRATCHUK
The defense forces of the south will continue to inflict fire damage on enemy locations, firing positions and rears.
During the day, we received confirmation that the enemy had decreased by:
• 114 occupants;
• 63 units of weapons and military equipment, namely:
2 tanks;
1 anti-tank missile complex "Sturm";
1 anti-aircraft missile complex "Buk";
1 launcher for the Buk air defense system;
19 guns;
1 mortar;
33 units of armored vehicles;
1 electronic warfare station;
4 aerial photography stations.

4 observation posts and a field supply point were destroyed.

Let's go forward, together - to Victory!

Then we came across a small Ukrainian document on the Leleka-100 UAV. Maybe it will be useful for someone. Leleka-100 UAV connection network diagram Each network node has its own IP address:
−10.10.10.1– router in the switching unit;
−10.10.10.2– target load;
−10.10.10.3– on-board computer;
−10.10.10.4– mobile control system (FCC);
−10.10.10.5– automatic antenna orientation module;
−10.10.10.6 – ground unit for receiving and transmitting telemetry signal;
−10.10.10.9– ground-based video signal receiving unit;
−10.10.10.10– UAV video signal transmission unit;
−10.10.10.11– video player and recorder (DFA);
−10.10.10.15– router in the antenna system.

Procedure for checking the connection of nodes:
Windows (FCC): Win+R > cmd > ping > IP addresses ( -t)
Linux (DFA): Ctrl+Alt+T> ping > IP addresses
Ctrl+C - Stop the transmission of information to this IP address. Revenge of good will

Forwarded from: PEOPLE OF RUSSIA🇷🇺
🇷🇺Health to all, dear PEOPLE OF RUSSIA🇷🇺A video has arrived from soldiers from the 19th Tank Regiment, whom we also help and bring a lot of what they need🪖At the moment, it’s no secret that the training camp is going very hard. In fact, it is clear that everyone is tired. The only thing, as I personally think, is one thing to be tired, being a fighter at the front in the trenches under fire, hiding from fpv drones, burying friends, in constant tension 24/7 for several months in a row. But it’s another thing to be tired, sitting at home, seeing your family every day, hugging your wife, talking with children...
Everyone has their own fatigue.
But it’s too early to relax. Our Victory is ahead and we all need to gather our strength. We will definitely win, but only by uniting for the sake of a common cause!

Now you need to purchase additional:
- diesel generators × 2 pcs;
- a large list of important repair equipment (discs for grinders, welding tools, wrenches, screwdrivers, etc.);
- consumables.

Bow to all of you, dear friends 🙏🏼Thank you for your constant contribution to the common cause, for your support and help. Together we are POWER!💪🏼GATHERING#17 “Spring”🍃(final part).

